 298|Error taxonomy:
 299|- `ServerSideError` / `ClientSideError` distinction is implicit in 
loader/action execution context.
+300|- `errorComponent` route option renders a component when a route 
loader/action throws.
+301|- `notFound()` helper throws a special `NotFoundError` caught by 
`notFoundComponent`.
 302|- Errors bubble to the nearest route `errorComponent`; the framework passes
the raw `error` object to the component.
 303|- `onError` callback in `createStartHandler` allows centralized logging.
 304|
 305|Telemetry conventions:
+306|- TanStack Start does not ship a built-in OTel integration. The recommended
pattern is to add an OpenTelemetry plugin in the Vinxi server entry 
(`https://vinxi.io/`).
+307|- Community convention: one span per request/loader/action with attributes 
`http.method`, `http.route`, `http.status_code`, `error.type`, `error.message`.
 308|- No framework-level event names; instrumentation is user-land.
 309|
